[h1]GK Raiding Expanded[/h1]

Capture pops. Strip planets. Wage wars the galaxy won't forget.

[h2]What This Mod Does[/h2]
[list]
[*][b]Splits pillaging from pop raiding[/b]: resources and captives now run through separate systems with their own rules, storage, and notifications
[*][b]Pillage in any war[/b]: pillage-capable empires can strip hostile worlds in any conflict
[*][b]Makes Pillage wars matter[/b]: the [b]Pillage[/b] war goal massively boosts resource extraction and guarantees a final surrender tribute
[*][b]Adds the Despoliation tradition tree[/b]: build into devastation, debris recovery, prize-taking admirals, and stronger baseline pillaging for empires that already raided before
[*][b]Keeps pop raiding focused[/b]: [b]Raiding[/b], [b]Reaping[/b], [b]Emancipation[/b], and [b]Robo-Liberation[/b] handle captives, not peace-time tribute
[*][b]Uses notification messages[/b]: invasion and surrender outcomes now report through cleaner vanilla-style notifications instead of popup event windows
[/list]

[h2]Pillaging[/h2]
[list]
[*] Loot scales with what the planet actually produces: energy, minerals, food, alloys, consumer goods, strategic resources, and more
[*] Fleets and armies both feed pillaging by inflicting devastation
[*] Every burst of fresh devastation can produce immediate plunder
[*] Invasions cash out what a world still had left to give without needing extra hidden mechanics
[*] [b]Pillage[/b] wars make all qualifying plunder far richer and force a final tribute out of surviving colonies on surrender
[*] Research and Unity are converted into Consumer Goods; Trade is especially valuable as plunder
[*] The [b]Despoliation[/b] tradition tree can grant pillaging to empires that do not already have a native pillage civic, or strengthen generic pillaging for empires that already could
[/list]

[h2]Pop Raiding[/h2]
[list]
[*][b]Raiding[/b]: standard captive-taking war. Capture pops during war and carry off the remainder on surrender up to the cap
[*][b]Reaping[/b]: unlimited pop capture. Brutal, extreme, and diplomatically toxic
[*][b]Emancipation[/b]: only enslaved pops may be taken
[*][b]Robo-Liberation[/b]: only robotic pops may be taken
[*] Allied raiders on the same war-goal side can all seize pops for themselves while still sharing one overall cap against the defender
[/list]

[h2]War Goals[/h2]
[list]
[*][b]Raiding[/b]: pop-focused peace outcome. Pillage-capable empires may still plunder resources during the war, but surrender gives captives, not tribute
[*][b]Pillage[/b]: pure resource war. No pop capture, but much richer pillaging and guaranteed surrender tribute
[*][b]Emancipation[/b]: enslaved pops only
[*][b]Robo-Liberation[/b]: robotic pops only
[*][b]Reaping[/b]: all pops, no limit
[/list]

[h2]Policies, Civics, and Traditions[/h2]
[list]
[*][b]Raiding Focus[/b]: choose between Plunder, No Pop-Raiding, Emancipation, or Robo-Liberation
[*][b]Robot Raiding[/b]: capture robots, organics only, or robots only
[*][b]Emancipators[/b]: dedicated slave-liberation raiders
[*][b]Robo-Liberators[/b]: dedicated machine-liberation raiders
[*][b]Harvest Incorporated / Harvesting Protocol[/b]: despoiler variants for Megacorps and Machine Intelligences
[*][b]Despoliation[/b]: a new tradition tree focused on devastation, debris recovery, raider admirals, and battlefield spoils
[/list]

[h2]Why Use It[/h2]

If you want raiding wars to feel distinct, readable, and worth specializing into, this mod gives you separate tools for stealing [i]people[/i] and stealing [i]wealth[/i], instead of collapsing both into the same opaque system.
